Anti-Semitic attacks worldwide have surged by 38 per cent, study reveals . 
 France remains the country with the highest number of incidents . 
 Last year it registered 164 anti-Semitic attacks, compared to 141 in 2013 . 
 Earlier this year, four hostages were killed at a Paris kosher supermarket . 
 Britain was home to 141 violent incidents, after registering 95 a year earlier . 
 